Last Updated: 04/03/2017 



Executive Summary
Somsak Chivavibul has served as Executive Vice President and Chief Decision Management Officer at Navient Solutions since March 2017. Most recently he was Executive Vice President and Chief Financial Officer of the company. He joined Navient, when Sallie Mae split up into two companies, Sallie Mae 
Personal Attributes and Interests

Chivavibul was 9 years old when his parents, who worked for the Thai embassy, moved to the United States for a four-year assignment. They liked the education system so much that they decided to stay so their three children could go to s 
Current Focus

New role: In March 2017, Chivavibul took over as Executive Vice President and Chief Decision Management Officer.  In this role, Somsak focuses on leveraging the Company’s data assets, infrastructure and talen 
Key Challenges

Downgraded SLABS: Navient funds most of its operation by manufacturing student loan asset-backed securities: bundling loans and selling them to investors as financial instruments. The SLABS are graded by bond rating age 
Biographical Highlights

Born c. 1967
Chivavibul holds a BS in accounting from the University of Maryland College Park (1984-1988) 
 





